obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[2A. Rule of construction regarding enactments not extending to Jammu and Kashmir.] --- Omitted`
  line `by the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, vide notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation`
  line `(Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (72579)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 4
  title `Punishment for keeping a brothel or allowing premises to be used as a brothel.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 6 (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72579&sectionno=3&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who keeps or manages, or acts or assists in the keeping or management of, a brothel shall be punishable on first conviction with rigorous imprisonment for a term of not less than one year and not more than three years and also with fine which may extend to two thousand rupees and in the event of a second or subsequent conviction, with rigorous imprisonment for a term of not less than two years and not more than five years and also with fine which may extend to two thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who-`
  line
  line `(a) being the tenant, lessee, occupier or person in charge of any premises, uses, or knowingly`
  line `allows any other person to use, such premises or any part thereof as a brothel, or`
  line
  line `(b) being the owner, lessor or landlord of any premises or the agent of such owner, lessor or landlord, lets the same or any part thereof with the knowledge that the same or any part thereof is intended to be used as a brothel, or is wilfully a party to the use of such premises or any part thereof as a brothel,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable on first conviction with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years and with fine which may extend to two thousand rupees and in the event of a second or subsequent conviction, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to five years and also with fine.`
  line
  line `^1[(2A) For the purposes of sub-section (2), it shall be presumed, until the contrary is proved, that any`
  line `person referred to in clause (a) or clause (b) of that sub-section, is knowingly allowing the premises or`
  line `any part thereof to be used as a brothel or, as the case may be, has knowledge that the premises or any`
  line `part thereof are beig used as a brothel, if,-`
  line
  line `(a) a report is published in a newspaper having circulation in the area in which such person`
  line `resides to the effect that the premises or any part thereof have been found to be used for prostitution`
  line `as a result of a search made under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) a copy of the list of all things found during the search referred to in clause (a) is given to such`
  line person.]
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, on conviction of any person referred to in clause (a) or clause (b) of sub-section (2) of any offence under that sub-section in respect of any premises or any part thereof, any lease or agreement under which such premises have been leased out or are held or occupied at the time of the commission of the offence, shall become void and inoperative with effect from the date of the said conviction.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (72580)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Punishment for living on the earnings of prostitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72580&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person over the age of eighteen`
  line `Years who knowingly lives, wholly or in part, on the`
  line `earnings of the prostitution of ^1[any other person]`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to one thousand rupees, or with both ^2[and where such earnings relate to the prostitution of a child`
  line `or a minor, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term of not less than seven years and not more`
  line `than ten years].`
  line
  line `^3[(2) Where any person over the age of eighteen`
  line `years is proved-`
  line
  line `(a) to be living with, or to be habitually in the company of, a prostitute; or`
  line
  line `(b) to have exercised control, direction or influence over the movements of a prostitute in such a`
  line `manner as to show that such person is aiding, abetting or compelling her prostitution; or`
  line
  line `(c) to be acting as a tout or pimp on behalf of a prostitute,`
  line `it shall be presumed, until the contrary is proved, that such person is knowingly living on the earnings of`
  line `prostitution of another person within the meaning of sub-section (1).]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Subs. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 7, for a woman or girl (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 46 of 1978, s. 4, for section 4 (w.e.f. 2-10-1979)`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (72581)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Procuring, inducing or taking person for the sake of prostitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72581&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Procuring, inducing or taking ^1[person] for the sake of prostitution.--(1) any person who--`
  line
  line `(a) procures or attempts to procure a ^1[person], whether with or without his consent, for the`
  line `purpose of prostitution; or`
  line
  line `(b) induces a ^1[person] to go from any place, with the intent that he may for the purpose of`
  line `prostitution become the inmate of, or frequent, a brothel; or`
  line
  line `(c) takes or attempts to take a ^1[person], or causes a ^1[person] to be taken, from one place to`
  line `another with a view to his carrying on, or being brought up to carry on prostitution; or`
  line
  line `(d) causes or induces a ^1[person] to carry on prostitution;`
  line
  line `^2[shall be punishable on conviction with rigorous imprisonment for a term of not less than three years and`
  line `not more than seven years and also with fine which may extend to two thousand rupees and if any offence`
  line `under this sub-section is committed against the will of any person, the punishment of imprisonment for a`
  line `term of seven years shall extend to imprisonment for a term of fourteen years:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the person in respect of whom an offence committed under this sub-section,--`
  line
  line `(i) is a child, the punishment provided under this sub-section shall extend to rigorous`
  line `imprisonment for a term of not less than seven years but may extend to life; and`
  line
  line `(ii) is a minor, the punishment provided under this sub-section shall extend to rigorous`
  line `imprisonment for a term of not less than seven years and not more than fourteen years;]`
  line
  line ^3*******
  line
  line `(3) An offence under this section shall be triable--`
  line
  line `(a) in the place from which a ^4[person] is procured, induced to go, taken or caused to be taken or`
  line `from which an attempt to procure or take such ^4[person] is made; or`
  line
  line `(b) in the place to which he may have gone as a result of the inducement or to which he is taken`
  line `or caused to be taken or an attempt to take him is made.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 4, for "women or girlsbqts (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line
  line `3. Omitted by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 4, for "woman or girl" (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (72582)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Detaining a person in premises where prostitution is carried on.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72582&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `6. Detaining a ^1[person] in premises where prostitution is carried on.--(1) Any person who detains ^2[any other person, whether with or without his consent],-- (a) in any brothel, or`
  line `(b) in or upon any premises with intent ^3[that such person may have sexual intercourse with a person who is not the spouse of such person],`
  line `shall be punishable ^3[on conviction, with imprisonment of either description for a term which shall not be less than seven years but which may be for life or for a term which may extend to ten years and shall also be liable to fine:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for adequate and special reasons to be mentioned in the judgment, impose a sentence of imprisonment for a term of less than seven years].`
  line
  line `^5[(2) Where any person is found with a child in a brothel, it shall be presumed, unless the contrary is proved, that he has committed an offence under sub-section (1).`
  line `(2A) Where a child or minor found in a brothel, is, on medical examination, detected to have been sexually abused, it shall be presumed, unless the contrary is proved, that the child or minor has been detained for purposes of prostitution or, as the case may be, has been sexually exploited for commercial purposes.]`
  line `(3) A person shall be presumed to detain a woman or girl in a brothel or in or upon any premises for the purpose of sexual intercourse with a man other than her lawful husband, if such person, with intent to compel or induce her to remain there,--`
  line `(a) withholds from her any jewellery, wearing apparel, money or other property belonging to her, or`
  line `(b) threatens her with legal proceedings if she takes away with her any jewellery, wearing apparel, money or other property lent or supplied to her by or by the direction of such person.`
  line `(4) Notwithstanding any law to the contrary, no suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie against such woman or girl at the instance of the person by whom she has been detained, for the recovery of any jewellery, wearing apparel or other property alleged to have been lent or supplied to or for such woman or girl or to have been pledged by such woman or girl or for the recovery of any money alleged to be payable by such woman or girl.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 4, for bqtswoman or girlbqts (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for bqtsany woman or girl, whether with or without his consentbqts (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 9, ibid. for "that she may have sexual intercourse with any man other than her lawful husband" (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (72583)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Prostitution in or in the vicinity of public places.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72583&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Any ^2[person], who carries on prostitution`
  line `and the person with whom such prostitution is carried on, in any premises,-`
  line
  line `(a) which are within the area or areas, notified under sub-section (3), or`
  line
  line `(b) which are within a distance of two hundred metres of any place of public religious worship,`
  line `educational institution, hostel, hospital, nursing home or such other public place of any kind as may`
  line `be notified in this behalf by the Commissioner of Police or magistrate in the manner prescribed,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months.]`
  line
  line `^3[(1A) Where an offence committed under sub-section (1) is in respect of a child or minor, the person`
  line `committing the offence shall be punishable with imprisonment of either description for a term which shall`
  line `not be less than seven years but which may be for life or for a term which may extend to ten years and`
  line `shall also be liable to fine:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for adequate and special reasons to be mentioned in the judgment,`
  line `impose a sentence of imprisonment for a term of less than seven years.]`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who`
  line
  line `(a) being the keeper of any public place knowingly permits prostitutes for purposes of their trade`
  line `to resort to or remain in such place; or`
  line
  line `(b) being the tenant, lessee, occupier or person in charge of any premises referred to in subsection (1) knowingly permits the same or any part thereof to be used for prostitution; or`
  line
  line `(c) being the owner, lessor or landlord, of any premises referred to in sub-section (1), or the agent`
  line `of such owner, lessor or landlord, lets the same or any part thereof with the knowledge that the same`
  line `or any part thereof may be used for prostitution, or is wilfully a party to such use,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable on first conviction with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months,`
  line `or with fine which may extend to two hundred rupees, or with both, and in the event of a second or`
  line `subsequent conviction with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months and also with`
  line `fine ^4[which may extend to two hundred rupees, and if the public place or premises happen to be a hotel,`
  line `the licence for carrying on the business of such hotel under any law for the time being in force shall also`
  line `be liable to be suspended for a period of not less than three months but which may extend to one year:`
  line
  line `Provided that if an offence committed under this sub-section is in respect of a child or minor in a hotel, such licence shall also be liable to be cancelled.`
  line
  line `Explanation.For the purposes of this sub-section, hotel shall have the meaning an in clause (6) of`
  line `section 2 of the Hotel-Receipts Tax Act, 1980 (54 of 1980).]`
  line
  line `^5[(3) The State Government may, having regard to the kinds of persons frequenting any area or areas`
  line `in the State, the nature and the density of population therein and other relevant considerations, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, direct that prostitution shall not be carried on in such area or areas as`
  line `may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a notification is issued under sub-section (3) in respect of any area or areas, the State`
  line `Government shall define the limits of such area or areas in the notification with reasonable certainty.`
  line
  line `(5) No such notification shall be issued so as to have effect from a date earlier than the expiry of a`
  line `period of ninety days after the date on which it is issued.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 46 of 1978, s. 5, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 2-10-1979).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 4, for woman or girl (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 10 (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for which may extend to two hundred rupees (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 46 of 1978, s. 5 (w.e.f. 2-10-1979).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (72584)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Seducing or soliciting for purpose of prostitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Proviso added by Act 44 of 1986, s. 11 (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72584&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, in any public place or within sight`
  line `of, and in such manner as to be seen or heard from any public place, whether from within any building or`
  line `house or not—`
  line
  line `(a) by words, gestures, wilful exposure of her person (whether by sitting by a window or on the`
  line `balcony of a building or house or in any other way), or otherwise tempts or endeavours to tempt, or`
  line `attracts or endeavours to attract the attention of, any person for the purpose of prostitution; or`
  line
  line `(b) solicits or molests any person, or loiters or acts in such manner as to cause obstruction or`
  line `annoyance to persons residing nearby or passing by such public place or to offend against public`
  line `decency, for the purpose of prostitution,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable on first conviction with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or`
  line `with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees, or with both, and in the event of a second or`
  line `subsequent conviction, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, and also with fine`
  line `which may extend to five hundred rupees:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that where an offence under this section is committed by a man, he shall be punishable`
  line `with imprisonment for a period of not less than seven days but which may extend to three months.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (72585)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Seduction of a person in custody.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72585&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line ^1***
  line
  line `Any person who ^2[having the custody, charge or care`
  line `of, or a position of authority over, any ^3[person], causes or aids or abets the seduction for prostitution of that ^3[person], ^4[shall be punishable on conviction with imprisonment of either description for a term which shall not be less than seven years but which may be for life or for a term which may extend to ten years and shall also be liable to fine:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for adequate and special reasons to be mentioned in the judgment, impose a sentence of imprisonment for a term of less than seven years].`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Brackets and figure (1) omitted by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 46 of 1978, s. 6, for certain words (w.e.f. 2-10-1979).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 4 for woman or girl (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 12, for certain words (w.e.f. 26-1-1987)`
  line
  line `5. Omitted by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (72606)
