  line `Traffic in Women and Girls (Amendment) Act, 1986 (44 of 1986) s. 13 (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (72609)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 15
  title `Special police officer and advisory body.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72609&sectionno=13&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be for each area to be specified by`
  line `the State Government in this behalf a special police officer appointed by or on behalf of that Government,`
  line `for dealing with offences under this Act in that area.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) The special police officer shall not be below the rank of an Inspector of Police.`
  line
  line `(2A) The District Magistrate may, if he considers it necessary or expedient so to do, confer upon any`
  line `retired police or military officer all or any of the powers conferred by or under this Act on a special police`
  line `officer, with respect to particular cases or classes of cases or to cases generally:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such power shall be conferred on,--`
  line
  line `(a) a retired police officer unless such officer, at the time of his retirement, was holding a post not`
  line `below the rank of an inspector;`
  line
  line `(b) a retired military officer unless such officer, at the time of his retirement, was holding a post`
  line `not below the rank of a commissioned officer.]`
  line
  line `(3) For the efficient discharge of his functions in relation to offences under this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) the special police officer of an area shall be assisted by such number of subordinate police`
  line `officers (including women police officers wherever practicable) as the State Government may think`
  line `fit; and`
  line
  line `(b) the State Government may associate with the special police officer a non-official advisory`
  line `body consisting of not more than five leading social welfare workers of that area (including women`
  line `social welfare workers wherever practicable) to advise him on questions of general importance`
  line `regarding the working of this Act.`
  line
  line `^2[(4) The Central Government may, for the purpose of investigating any offence under this Act or`
  line `under any other law for the time being in force dealing with sexual exploitation of persons and committed`
  line `in more than one State, a point such number of police officers as trafficking police officers and they shall`
  line `exercise all the powers and discharge all the functions as are exercisable by special police officers under`
  line `this Act with the modification that they shall exercise such powers and discharge such functions in`
  line `relation to the whole of India.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 46 of 1978, s. 9, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 2-10-1979).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 15 (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (72589)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 16
  title `Offences to be cognizable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72589&sectionno=14&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in ^1[the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974)], any offence punishable under this Act shall be deemed to be a cognizable`
  line `offence within the meaning of that Code:`
  line
  line `Provided that, notwithstanding anything contained in that Code,--`
  line
  line `(i) arrest without warrant may be made only by the special police officer or under his direction or`
  line `guidance, or subject to his prior approval;`
  line
  line `(ii) when the special police officer requires any officer subordinate to him to arrest without`
  line `warrant otherwise than in his presence any person for an offence under this Act, he shall give that`
  line `subordinate officer an order in writing, specifying the person to be arrested and the offence for which`
  line `the arrest is being made; and the latter officer, before arresting the person, shall inform him of the`
  line `substance of the order and, on being required by such person, show him the order;`
  line
  line `(iii) any police officer not below the rank of ^2[sub-inspector] specially authorised by the special`
  line `police officer may, if he has reason to believe that on account of delay involved in obtaining the order`
  line `of the special police officer, any valuable evidence relating to any offence under this Act is likely to`
  line `be destroyed or concealed, or the person who has committed or is suspected to have committed the`
  line `offence is likely to escape, or if the name and address of such a person is unknown or there is reason`
  line `to suspect that a false name or address has been given, arrest the person concerned without such`
  line `order, but in such a case he shall report, as soon as may be, to the special police officer the arrest and`
  line `the circumstances in which the arrest was made.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 46 of 1978, s. 10, for certain words (w.e.f. 2-10-1979).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for "inspector" (w.e.f. 2-10-1979).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (72590)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 17
  title `Search without warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72590&sectionno=15&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, whenever the special police officer ^1[or the trafficking police officer, as the case may be,]`
  line
  line `has reasonable grounds for believing that an offence punishable under this Act has been or is being`
  line `committed in respect of a ^2[person[ living in any premises, and that search of the premises with warrant`
  line `cannot be made without undue delay, such officer may, after recording the grounds of his belief, enter and`
  line `search such premises without a warrant.`
  line
  line `(2) Before making a search under sub-section (1), the special police officer ^1[or the trafficking police`
  line `officer, as the case may be,] shall call upon two or more respectable inhabitants (at least one of whom`
  line `shall be a woman) of the locality in which the place to be searched is situate, to attend and witness the`
  line `search, and may issue an order in writing to them or any of them so to do:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that the requirement as to the respectable inhabitants being from the locality in which the`
  line `place to be searched is situate shall not apply to a woman required to attend and witness the search.]`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who, without reasonable cause, refuses or neglects, to attend and witness a search`
  line `under this section, when called upon to do so by an order in writing delivered or tendered to him, shall be`
  line `deemed to have committed an offence under section 187 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `^4[(4) The special police officer or the trafficking police officer, as the case may be, entering any`
  line `premises under sub-section (1) shall be entitled to remove therefrom all the persons found therein.]`
  line
  line `(5) The special police officer ^5[or the trafficking police officer, as the case may be,] after`
  line `removing ^6[the ^7[person]] under sub-section (4) shall forthwith produce him before the appropriate`
  line magistrate.
  line
  line `^5[(5A) Any person who is produced before a magistrate under sub-section (5), shall be examined by a`
  line `registered medical practitioner for the purposes of determination of the age of such person, or for the`
  line `detection of any injuries as a result of sexual abuse or for the presence of any sexually transmitted`
  line diseases.
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this sub-section, "registered medical practitioner" has the same meaning as in the`
  line `Indian Medical Council Act, 1956 (102 of 1956).]`
  line
  line `(6) The special police officer ^5[or the trafficking police officer, as the case may be,] and other persons`
  line `taking part in, or attending, and witnessing a search shall not be liable to any civil or criminal proceedings`
  line `against them in respect of anything lawfully done in connection with, or for the purpose of, the search.`
  line
  line `^5[(6A) The special police officer or the trafficking police officer, as the case may be, making a search`
  line `under this section shall be accompanied by at least two women police officers, and where any woman or`
  line `girl removed under sub-section (4) is required to be interrogated, it shall be done by a woman police`
  line `officer and if no woman police officer is available, the interrogation shall be done only in the presence of`
  line `a lady member of a recognised welfare institution or organisation.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this sub-section and section 17A,"recognised welfare institution or`
  line `organisation" means such institution or organisation as may be recognised in this behalf by the State`
  line Government.]
  line
  line `^8[(7) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), shall, so far as may be,`
  line `apply to any search under this section as they apply to any search made under the authority of a warrant`
  line `issued under section 94 of the said Code.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 16 (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "women or girl" (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 46 of 1978, s. 11 (w.e.f. 2-10-1979).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 16, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 16 (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 46 of 1978, s. 11, for "the girl" (w.e.f. 2-10-1979).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 4, for "woman or girl" (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 46 of 1978, s. 11 (w.e.f. 2-10-1979).`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (72591)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Rescue of person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72591&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `^1[16. Rescue of ^2[person].--(1) Where a magistrate has reason to believe from information received`
  line `from the police or from any other person authorised by the State Government in this behalf or otherwise,`
  line `that ^3[any person is living, or is carrying on, or is being made to carry on, prostitution in a brothel,] he`
  line `may direct a police officer not below the rank of a sub-inspector, to enter such brothel, and to remove`
  line `therefrom such ^2[person] and produce him before him.`
  line
  line `(2) The police officer, after removing the ^2[person], shall forthwith produce him before the magistrate`
  line `issuing the order.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 46 of 1978, s. 12, for sections 16 and 17 (w.e.f. 2-10-1979).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 4, for "woman or girl" (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 17, for clause (a) and (b) (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (72592)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title `Intermediate custody of persons removed under section 15 or rescued under section 16.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72592&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `17. Intermediate custody of^1[persons] removed under section 15 or rescued under section 16.--`
  line `(1) When the special police officer removing a ^2[person] under sub-section (4) of section 15 or a police`
  line `officer rescuing a ^2[person] under sub-section (1) of section 16, is for any reason unable to produce him`
  line `before the appropriate magistrate as required by sub-section (5) of section 15, or before the magistrate`
  line `issuing the order under sub-section (2) of section 16, he shall forthwith produce him before the nearest`
  line `magistrate of any class, who shall pass such orders as he deems proper for his safe custody until he is`
  line `produced before the appropriate magistrate, or, as the case may be, the magistrate issuing the order:`
  line
  line `Provided that no ^2[person] shall be--`
  line
  line `(i) detained in custody under this sub-section for a period exceeding ten days from the date of the`
  line `order under this sub-section; or`
  line
  line `(ii) restored to or placed in the custody of a person who may exercise a harmful influence over`
  line him.
  line
  line `(2) When the ^2[person] is produced before the appropriate magistrate under sub-section (5) of section`
  line `15 or the magistrate under sub-section (2) of section 16, he shall, after giving him an opportunity of being`
  line `heard, cause an inquiry to be made as to the correctness of the information received under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 16, the age, character and antecedents of the ^2[person] and the suitability of his parents,`
  line `guardian or husband for taking charge of him and the nature of the influence which the conditions in his`
  line `home are likely to have on him if he is sent home, and, for this purpose, he may direct a probation officer`
  line `appointed under the Probation of Offenders Act, 1958 (20 of 1958), to inquire into the above`
  line `circumstances and into the personality of the ^2[person] and the prospects of his rehabilitation.`
  line
  line `(3) The magistrate may, while an inquiry is made into a case under sub-section (2), pass such orders`
  line `as he deems proper for the safe custody of the ^2[person]:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that where a person rescued under section 16 is a child or minor, it shall be open to the`
  line `magistrate to place such child or minor in any institution established or recognised under any Children`
  line `Act, for the time being in force in any State for the safe custody of children:`
  line
  line `Provided further that, no ^2[person] shall be kept in custody for this purpose for a period exceeding`
  line `three weeks from the date of such an order, and no ^2[person] shall be kept in the custody of a person likely`
  line `to have a hurmful influence over him.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the magistrate is satisfied, after making an inquiry as required under sub-section (2),--`
  line
  line `(a) that the information received is correct; and`
  line
  line `(b) that he is in need of care and protection,`
  line
  line `he may, subject to the provisions of sub-section (5), make an order that such`
  line `^2[person] be detained for`
  line `such period, being not less than one year and not more than three years, as may be specified in the order,`
  line `in a protective home, or in such other custody as he shall, for reasons to be recorded in writing, consider`
  line `suitable:`
  line
  line `Provided that such custody shall not be that of a person or body of persons of a religious persuasion`
  line `different from that of the ^2[personic and that those entrusted with the custody of the ^2[person] including the`
  line `persons in charge of a protective home, may be required to enter into a bond which may, were necessary`
  line `and feasible, contain undertakings based on directions relating to the proper care, guardianship, education,`
  line `training and medical and psychiatric treatment of the ^2[person] as well as supervision by a person`
  line `appointed by the court, which will be in force for a period, not exceeding three years.`
  line
  line `(5) In discharging his functions under sub-section (2), a magistrate may summon a panel of five`
  line `respectable persons, three of whom shall, wherever practicable, be women, to assist him; and may, for`
  line `this purpose, keep a list of experienced social welfare workers, particularly women social welfare`
  line `workers, in the field of suppression of immoral traffic in ^1[persons].`
  line
  line `(6) An appeal against an order made under sub-section (4) shall lie to the Court of Session whose`
  line `decision on such appeal shall be final.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. s. 4, ibid., for "women and girls" (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 4, for "woman or girl" (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., "Provide that" (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_17_a:
  sectionId (72610)
  sectionNo 17A
  orderNo 20
  title `Conditions to be observed before placing persons rescued under section 16 to parents or guardians.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 19, ibid. (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72610&sectionno=17A&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content:
  string
  line `^1]17A. Conditions to be observed before placing persons rescued under section 16 to parents or`
  line `guardians.--Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2) of section 17, the magistrate making`
  line `an inquiry under section 17 may, before passing an order for handing over any person rescued under`
  line `section 16 to the parents, guardian or husband, satisfy himself about the capacity or genuineness of the`
  line `parents, guardian or husband to keep such person by causing an investigation to be made by a recognised`
  line `welfare institution or organisation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (72594)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 21
  title `Closure of brothel and eviction of offenders from the premises.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72594&sectionno=18&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) A magistrate may, on`
  line `receipt of information from the police or otherwise, that any house, room, place or any portion thereof`
  line `within a distance of ^1]two hundred metres] of any public place referred to in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 7, is being run or used as a brothel by any person or is being used by prostitutes for carrying on their trade, issue notice on the owner, lessor or landlord of such house, room, place or portion or the agent`
  line `of the owner, lessor or landlord or on the tenant, lessee, occupier of, or any other person incharge of such`
  line `house, room, place, or portion, to show cause within seven days of the receipt of the notice why the same`
  line `should not be attached for improper user thereof; and if, after hearing the person concerned, the`
  line `magistrate is satisfied that the house, room, place or portion is being used as a brothel or for carrying on`
  line `prostitution, then the magistrate may pass orders--`
  line
  line `(a) directing eviction of the occupier within seven days of the passing of the order from the`
  line `house, room, place or portion;`
  line
  line `(b) directing that before letting it out during the period of one year ^2]or in a case where a child or`
  line `minor has been found in such house, room, place or portion during a search under section 15, during`
  line `the period of three years], immediately after the passing of the order, the owner, lessor or landlord or`
  line `the agent of the owner, lessor or landlord shall obtain the previous approval of the magistrate:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the magistrate finds that the owner, lessor or landlord as well as the agent of the`
  line `owner, lessor or landlord, was innocent of the improper user of the house, room, place or portion, he may`
  line `cause the same to be restored to the owner, lessor or landlord, or the agent of the owner, lessor or`
  line `landlord, with a direction that the house, room, place or portion shall not be leased out, or otherwise given`
  line `possession of, to or for the benefit of the person who was allowing the improper user therein.`
  line
  line `(2) A court convicting a person of any offence under section 3 or section 7 may pass order under subsection (1) without further notice to such person to show cause as required in that sub-section.`
  line
  line `(3) Orders passed by the magistrate or court under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall not be`
  line `subject to appeal and shall not be stayed or set aside by the order of any court, civil or criminal and the`
  line `said orders shall cease to have validity after the ^3]expiry of one year or three years, as the case may be]:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a conviction under section 3 or section 7 is set aside on appeal on the ground that`
  line `such house, room, place or any portion thereof is not being run or used as a brothel or is not being used by`
  line `prostitutes for carrying on their trade, any order passed by the trial court under sub-section (1) shall also`
  line `be set aside.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, when a`
  line `magistrate passes an order under sub-section (1), or a court passes an order under sub-section (2), any`
  line `lease or agreement under which the house, room, place or portion is occupied at the time, shall become`
  line `void and inoperative.`
  line
  line `(5) When an owner, lessor or landlord, or the agent of such owner, lessor or landlord fails to comply`
  line `with a direction given under clause (b) of sub-section (1), he shall be punishable with fine which may`
  line `extend to five hundred rupees or when he fails to comply with a direction under the proviso to that subsection, he shall be deemed to have committed an offence under clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 3`
  line `or clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 7, as the case may be, and punished accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 46 of 1978, s. 13, for "two hundred yards" (w.e.f. 2-10-1979).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 20 (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 20, ibid., for "expiry of one year" (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (72595)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 22
  title `Application for being kept in a protective home or provided care and protection by court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72595&sectionno=19&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `^1[19. Application for being kept in a protective home or provided care and protection by`
  line `court.--(1) A ^2[person] who is carrying on, or is being made to carry on, prostitution, may make an`
  line `application, to the magistrate within the local limits of whose jurisdiction he is carrying on, or is being`
  line `made to carry on prostitution, for an order that he may be--`
  line
  line `(a) kept in a protective home, or`
  line
  line `(b) provided care and protection by the court in the manner specified in sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(2) The magistrate may, pending inquiry under sub-section (3), direct that the ^2[person] be kept in`
  line `such custody as he may consider proper, having regard to the circumstances of the case.`
  line
  line `(3) If the magistrate, after hearing the applicant and making such inquiry as he may consider`
  line `necessary, including an inquiry by a probation officer appointed under the Probation of Offenders Act,`
  line `1958 (20 of 1958), into the personality, conditions of home and prospects of rehabilitation of the`
  line `applicant, is satisfied that an order should be made under this section, he shall, for reasons to be recorded,`
  line `make an order that the applicant be kept,--`
  line
  line `(i) in a protective home, or`
  line
  line `(ii) in a corrective institution, or`
  line
  line `(iii) under the supervision of a person appointed by the magistrate,`
  line
  line `for such period as may be specified in the order.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 46 of 1978, s. 14, for section 19 (w.e.f. 2-10-1979).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 4, for "woman or girl" (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (72596)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 23
  title `Removal of prostitute from any place.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 4, for "woman or girl" (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72596&sectionno=20&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) A magistrate on receiving information that`
  line `any ^1]person] residing in or frequenting any place within the local limits of his jurisdiction, is a prostitute,`
  line `may record the substance of the information received and issue a notice to such ^1]person] requiring him to`
  line `appear before the magistrate and show cause why he should not be required to remove himself from the`
  line `place and be prohibited from re-entering it.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notice issued under sub-section (1) shall be accompanied by a copy of the record aforesaid,`
  line `and the copy shall be served along with the notice on the ^1]person] against whom the notice is issued.]`
  line
  line `(3) The magistrate shall, after the service of the notice referred to in sub-section (2), proceed to`
  line `inquire into the truth of the information received, and after giving the ^1]person] an opportunity of`
  line `adducing evidence, take such further evidence as he thinks fit, and if upon such inquiry it appears to him`
  line `that such ^1]person] is a prostitute and that it is necessary in the interests of the general public that`
  line `such ^1]person] should be required to remove himself therefrom and be prohibited form re-entering the`
  line `same, the magistrate shall, by order in writing communicated to the ^1]person] in the manner specified`
  line `therein, require him after a date (to be specified in the order) which shall not be less than seven days from`
  line `the date of the order, to remove himself from the place to such place whether within or without the local`
  line `limits of his jurisdiction, by such route or routes and within such time as may be specified in the order and`
  line `also prohibit him from re-entering the place without the permission in writing of the magistrate having`
  line `jurisdiction over such place.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever,--`
  line
  line `(a) fails to comply with an order issued under this section, within the period specified therein, or`
  line `whilst an order prohibiting him from re-entering a place without permission is in force, re-enters the`
  line `place without such permission, or`
  line
  line `(b) knowing that any ^1]person] has, under this section, been required to removehimself from the`
  line `place and has not obtained the requisite permission to re-enter it, harbours or conceals such ^1]person]`
  line `in the place,`
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to two hundred rupees not in the case of a continuing`
  line `offence with an additional fine which may extend to twenty rupees for every day after the first during`
  line `which he has persisted in the offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (72597)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 24
  title `Protective homes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72597&sectionno=21&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, in its discretion establish ^1[as many`
  line `protective homes and corrective institutions under this Act as it thinks fit and such homes and`
  line `institutions], when established, shall be maintained in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) No person or no authority other than the State Government shall, after the commencement of this`
  line `Act, establish or maintain any ^2]protective home or corrective institution] except under and in accordance`
  line `with the conditions of a licence issued under this section by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may, on application made to it in this behalf by a person or authority issue`
  line `to such person or authority, a licence in the prescribed form for establishing and maintaining or as the case may be, for maintaining a ^3[protective home or corrective institution] and a licence so issued may`
  line `contain such conditions as the State Government may think fit to impose in accordance with the rules`
  line `made under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that any such condition may require that the management of the ^3[protective home or`
  line `corrective institution] shall, wherever practicable, be entrusted to women:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a person or authority maintaining any protective home at the commencement of`
  line `this Act shall be allowed a period of six months from such commencement to make an application for`
  line `such licence:`
  line
  line `^4[Provided also that a person or authority maintaining any corrective institution at the commencement`
  line `of the Suppression of Immoral Traffic in Women and Girls (Amendment) Act, 1978 (46 of 1978), shall be`
  line `allowed a period of six months from such commencement to make an application for such licence.]`
  line
  line `(4) Before issuing a licence the State Government may require such officer or authority as it may`
  line `appoint for this purpose, to make a full and complete investigation in respect of the application received`
  line `in this behalf and report to it the result of such investigation and in making any such investigation the`
  line `officer or authority shall follow such procedure as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) A licence, unless sooner revoked, shall remain in force for such period as may be specified in the`
  line `licence and may, on application made in this behalf at least thirty days before the date of its expiration, be`
  line `renewed for a like period.`
  line
  line `(6) No licence issued or renewed under this Act shall be transferable.`
  line
  line `(7) Where any person or authority to whom a licence has been granted under this Act or any agent or`
  line `servant of such person or authority commits a breach of any of the conditions thereof or any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or of any of the rules made under this Act, or where the State Government is not`
  line `satisfied with the condition, management or superintendence of any ^3[protective home or corrective`
  line `institution], the State Government may, without prejudice to any other penalty which may have been`
  line `incurred under this Act, for reasons to be recorded, revoke the licence by order in writing:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made until an opportunity is given to the holder of the licence to`
  line `show cause why the licence shall not be revoked.`
  line
  line `(8) Were a licence in respect of a ^3]protective home or corrective institution] has been revoked under`
  line `the foregoing sub-section such ^3[protective home or corrective institution] shall cease to function from the`
  line `date of such revocation.`
  line
  line `(9) Subject to any rules that may be made in this behalf, the State Government may also vary or`
  line `amend any licence issued or renewed under this Act.`
  line `^4[(9A) The State Government or an authority authorised by it in this behalf may, subject to any rules`
  line `that may be made in this behalf, transfer an inmate of a protective home to another protective home or to`
  line `a corrective institution or an inmate of a corrective institution to another corrective institution or to a`
  line `protective home, where such transfer is considered desirable having regard to the conduct of the person to`
  line `be transferred, the kind of training to be imparted and other circumstances of the case:`
  line
  line `Provided that,--`
  line
  line `(a) no ^5[person] who is transferred under this sub-section shall be required to stay in the home or`
  line `institution to which he is transferred for a period longer than he was required to stay in the home or`
  line `institution from which he was transferred;`
  line
  line `(b) reasons shall be recorded for every order of transfer under this sub-section.]`
  line
  line `(10) Whoever establishes or maintains a ^3[protective home or corrective institution] except in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this section, shall be punishable in the case of a first offence with fine`
  line `which may extend to one thousand rupees and in the case of second or subsequent offence with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine which may extend to two thousand`
  line `rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by 46 of 1978, s. 15, for "as many protective homes under this Act as it thinks it and such homes" (w.e.f. 2-10-1979).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "protective home" (w.e.f. 2-10-1979).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 46 of 1978, s. 15, for "protective home" (w.e.f. 2-10-1979).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-10-1978).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 4, for "woman or girl" (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_21_a:
  sectionId (72598)
  sectionNo 21A
  orderNo 25
  title `Production of records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 21 (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72598&sectionno=21A&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_21_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[21A. Production of records.--Every person or authority who is licensed under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 21 to establish or maintain, or as the case may be, for maintaining, a protective home or corrective`
  line `institution shall, whenever required by a court, produce the records and other documents maintained by`
  line `such home or institution before such court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (72599)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 26
  title Trials.
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 46 of 1978, s. 16, for "a magistrate as defined in clause (c) of section 2" (w.e.f. 2-10-1979).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72599&sectionno=22&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `No court, inferior to that of ^1[a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the`
  line `first class] shall try any offence under section 3, section 4, section 5, section 6, section 7 or section 8.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_a:
  sectionId (72600)
  sectionNo 22A
  orderNo 27
  title `Power to establish special courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 17, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-10-1979).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72600&sectionno=22A&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[22A. Power to establish Special Courts.--(1) If the State Government is satisfied that it is`
  line `necessary for the purpose of providing for speedy trial of offences under this Act in any district or`
  line `metropolitan area, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette and after consultation with the High`
  line `Court, establish one or more courts of Judicial Magistrates of the first class, or, as the case may be,`
  line `Metropolitan Magistrates, in such district or metropolitan area.`
  line
  line `(2) Unless otherwise directed by the High Court, a court established under sub-section (1) shall`
  line `exercise jurisdiction only in respect of cases under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), the jurisdiction and powers of the presiding officer of`
  line `a court established under sub-section (1) in any district or metropolitan area shall extend throughout the`
  line `district or the metropolitan area, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the foregoing provisions of this section a court established under sub-section (1) in any`
  line `district or metropolitan area shall be deemed to be a court established under sub-section (1) of section 11,`
  line `or as the case may be, sub-section (1) of section 16, of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974),`
  line `and the provisions of that Code shall apply accordingly in relation to such courts.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, "High Court" has the same meaning as in clause (e) of section 2 of the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_aa:
  sectionId (72601)
  sectionNo 22AA
  orderNo 28
  title `Power of Central Government to establish special courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_aa_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 22 (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72601&sectionno=22AA&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_22_aa_content:
  string
  line `^1[22AA. Power of Central Government to establish special courts.--(1) If the Central`
  line `Government is satisfied that it is necessary for the purpose of providing for speedy trial of offences under`
  line `this Act and committed in more than one State, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette and after`
  line `consultation with the High Court concerned, establish one or more courts of Judicial Magistrates of the`
  line `first class or Metropolitan Magistrates for the trial of such offences.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of section 22A, shall, so far as may be, apply to the courts established under subsection (1) as they apply to courts established under that section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_b:
  sectionId (72602)
  sectionNo 22B
  orderNo 29
  title `Power of Court to try cases summarily.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 22 (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72602&sectionno=22B&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_22_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[22B.Power of Court to try cases summarily.--Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), the State Government may, if it considers it necessary so to do,`
  line `direct that offences under this Act shall be tried in a summary way by a magistrate including the`
  line `presiding officer of a court established under sub-section (1) of section 22A and the provisions of Section`
  line `262 to 265 (both inclusive) of the said Code shall, as far as may be, apply to such trial:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of any conviction in a summary trial under this section it shall be lawful for`
  line `the magistrate to pass a sentence of imprisonment for a term not exceeding one year:`
  line
  line `Provided further that when at the commencement of, or in the course of, a summary trial under this`
  line `section, it appears to the magistrate that the nature of the case is such that a sentence of imprisonment for`
  line `a term exceeding one year may have to be passed or that it is, for any other reason, undesirable to try the`
  line `case summarily, the magistrate shall, after hearing the parties, record an order to that effect and thereafter`
  line `recall any witness, who may have been examined and proceed to hear or rehear the case in the manner`
  line `provided by the said Code.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (72603)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72603&sectionno=23&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the notification of any place as a public place;`
  line
  line `^1[(b) the placing in custody of persons for whose safe custody orders have been passed under subsection (1) of section 17 and their maintenance;]`
  line
  line `^2[(bb) the discharge of an offender under sub-section (3) of section 10A from a corrective`
  line `institution and the form of licence to be granted to such offender;]`
  line
  line `^3[(c) the detention and keeping in protective homes or, as the case may be, in corrective`
  line `institutions of ^4[persons] under this Act and their maintenance;]`
  line
  line `(d) the carrying out of the provisions of section 11 regarding notification of residence or change`
  line `of or absence from residence by released convicts;`
  line
  line `(e) the delegation of authority to appoint the special police officer under sub-section (1) of section`
  line 13;
  line
  line `(f) the carrying into effect of the provisions of section 18;`
  line
  line `^5[(g) (i) the establishment, maintenance, management and superintendence of protective homes`
  line `and corrective institutions under section 21 and the appointment, powers and duties of persons`
  line `employed in such homes or institutions;`
  line
  line `(ii) the form in which an application for a licence may be made and the particulars to be`
  line `contained in such application;`
  line
  line `(iii) the procedure for the issue or renewal of a licence, the time within which such licence`
  line `shall be issued or renewed and the procedure to be followed in making a full and complete`
  line `investigation in respect of an application for a licence;`
  line
  line `(iv) the form of a licence and the conditions to be specified therein;`
  line
  line `(v) the manner in which the accounts of a protective home and a corrective institution shall be`
  line `maintained and audited;`
  line
  line `(vi) the maintenance of registers and statements by a licensee and the form of such registers`
  line `and statements;`
  line
  line `(vii) the care, treatment, maintenance, training, instruction, control and discipline of the`
  line `inmates of protective homes and corrective institutions;`
  line
  line `(viii) the visits to and communication with such inmates;`
  line
  line `(ix) the temporary detention of ^4[persons] sentenced to detention in protective homes or in`
  line `corrective institutions until arrangements are made for sending them to such homes or`
  line institutions;
  line
  line `(x) the transfer of an inmate from,--`
  line
  line `(a) one protective home to another, or to a corrective institution,`
  line
  line `(b) one corrective institution to another or to a protective home,`
  line `under sub-section (9A) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(xi) the transfer in pursuance of an order of the court from a protective home or a corrective`
  line `institution to a prison of a ^6[person] found to be incorrigible or exercising bad influence upon`
  line `other inmates of that protective home or the corrective institution and the period of his detention`
  line `in such prison;`
  line
  line `(xii) the transfer to a protective home or corrective institution of ^7[persons] sentenced under`
  line `section 7 or section 8 and the period of their detention in such home or institution;`
  line
  line `(xiii) the discharge of inmates from a protective home or corrective institution either`
  line `absolutely or subject to conditions, and their arrest in the event of breach of such conditions;`
  line
  line `(xiv) the grant of permission to inmates to absent themselves for short periods;`
  line
  line `(xv) the inspection of protective homes and corrective institutions and other institutions in`
  line `which ^6[persons] may be kept, detained and maintained;]`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) In making any rule under clause (d) or clause (g) of sub-section (2) the State Government may`
  line `provide that a breach thereof shall be punishable with fine which may extend to two hundred and fifty`
  line rupees.
  line
  line `(4) All rules made under this Act shall, as soon as may be, after they are made, be laid before the`
  line `State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 23, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 46 of 1978, s. 18 (w.e.f. 2-10-1979).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for clause (c) (w.e.f. 2-10-1979).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 4, for "women and girl" (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by 46 of 1978, s. 18, for clause (g) (w.e.f. 2-10-1979).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 44 of 1986, s. 4, for "woman or girl" (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "women and girl" (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (72604)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 31
  title `Act not to be in derogation of certain other Acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72604&sectionno=24&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall be construed to be`
  line `in derogation of the provisions of the Refermatory Schools Act, 1897 (8 of 1897), or any State Act`
  line `enacted in modification of the said Act or otherwise, relating to juvenile offenders.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (72605)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 32
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "women and girl" (w.e.f. 26-1-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535&sectionId=72605&sectionno=25&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_0_00015_1956104_1673601098535
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the date of the coming into force in any State of the`
  line `provisions other than section 1 of this Act, all State Acts relating to suppression of immoral traffic`
  line `in ^1[persons] or to the prevention of prostitution, in force in that State immediately before such date shall`
  line `stand repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal by this Act of any State Act referred to in sub-section (1), anything`
  line `done or any action taken (including any direction given, any register, rule or order made, any restriction`
  line `imposed) under the provisions of such State Act shall in so far as such thing or action is not inconsistent`
  line `with the provisions of this Act be deemed to have been done or taken under the provisions of this Act, as`
  line `if the said provisions were in force when such thing was done or such action was taken and shall continue`
  line `in force accordingly until superseded by anything done or any action taken under this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section the expression “State Act” includes a "Provincial Act".`
